Description: PCA applies the highest quality climate research to solve problems impacting global markets and people in need
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: PCA is a global leader in weather and climate information services, revolutionizing the quality and optimization of weather, water, and climate data.  It is active in InsureTech, AgTech, government and other major global markets. In early 2017, Princeton University Executive-in-Residence Joe Studholme met Eric Wood, the Susan Dod Brown Professor of Civil and Environmental Engineering at the University. After determining that there was a strong market need for improved climate data products, they founded the company with Professor Justin Sheffield. They worked with Princeton University’s Office of Technology and Licensing to define, patent, and license the University’s IP for the exclusive commercial use of Princeton Climate Analytics, Inc. Once the license was in place in late 2017,  key data science and technology team joined the company and began rapid commercial development and deployment of the Princeton Hydrological Engine (PHE). PCA’s first customers included the World Bank, the InterAmerican Development Bank, the EU/Copernicus Project and others as the company delivered the first in a series of high-quality climate data and analysis products. The company supports ongoing research via its PCA Labs division, which continues to produce the world’s most advanced, scientifically validated hydrology data and analysis products. Additionally, the company continues its commitment to serving underdeveloped communities by providing pro-bono data analysis, tools, monitoring and support to agricultural users in Africa via its ongoing UNESCO partnership.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Financial Services, Government and Military, Information Technology

Description: SpamHero is a professional spam filtering accuracy while lowering the cost to domain and business owners.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: SpamHero is a spam filtering solution for businesses and domain owners. SpamHero's was developed by two brothers, Curtis and Jeremy O'Reilly.  After 13 years in the web hosting industry they've witnessed first hand the frustrations that business owners have over the cost of fighting spam, and the lackluster performance of existing solutions. What makes SpamHero different is that it is powered by a team of human spam-fighting technicians who are updating the filter rules several times a day.  Over 2 million rules have been compiled so far.   Unlike "robotic" algorithms that can sometimes mistake real email for spam, each rule is carefully crafted in such a way that  real email does not get blocked. Because SpamHero is a hosted solution, it requires no new hardware or software installed at a clientâ€:tm:s location.   The client changes what is known as their domain's MX record so that email flows through SpamHero's filtering servers before it reaches the domain's real mail server.   The filtering service all includes a Web 2.0 email quarantine that allows users to view the spam that is caught by the filter. Pricing for the service starts at $4.95 per month for domain-wide filtering, which the company founders believe is much less than similar solutions on the market.

Description: SonoPlot, Inc. manufactures and sells precision picoliter fluid spotting and plotting instruments for use in microelectronics and life
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: SonoPlot, Inc. manufactures and sells precision picoliter fluid spotting and plotting instruments for use in microelectronics and life sciences research applications. It offers GIX Microplotter Desktop and GIX Microplotter, an entry-level and high-precision picoliter dispensers that print micro circuitry on a desktop for research and development or deposit high-density grids of biomolecules, such as DNA or proteins for fabrication of microarrays; and SonoCoat Treated Slides, a series of surface treatment processes for attaching biomolecules to a range of materials, such as glass, stainless steel, polymers, diamond, and carbon nanotubes. The company’s products are used in life sciences applications, such as chemical treatment of oxide and unreactive polymer surfaces, mass spectrometry enhancement via small spots, spotting DNA at a high resolution for microarray fabrication, and spotting proteins for an ELISA-type microarray assay; and polymers and printed electronics applications, including deposition of catalyst for carbon nanotube growth, drawing a polymer-based blue led, and printing lines of nanometallic ink for conductive electronic traces. SonoPlot, Inc. was incorporated in 2003 and is headquartered in Middleton, Wisconsin.
